[heard] nQoYJ_00001.mp3: this meant you could finally wear a simple kimono and follow your quote older sister an established geisha to the teahouses your job was to watch to observe you sat silently in the corner of the room during banquets absorbing everything how she poured the sake never letting a guest cup run empty how she laughed at a client's joke making him feel like the wittiest man in the world how she deflected an inappropriate comment with a graceful turn of phrase you were learning that a geisha's true art isn't just dance or music it's the art of creating a perfect moment for someone else then comes the misedashi your official debut as a maiko an apprentice geisha it's a day of overwhelming ceremony and sensation the first thing you feel is the weight your kimono is a magnificent burden of silk and brocade weighing up to 20 kilograms the obi the wide sash is nearly seven meters long and tied in a complex knot that presses into your back you can barely breathe then comes the face an older sister paints your skin with a thick white paste called oshiroi it feels cool and heavy a mask that hides the young girl underneath what you don't know in this year of 1935 is that this beautiful white powder is made with lead with every application a little bit of poison seeps into your skin your eyebrows are drawn on with charcoal
