[heard] nQoYJ_00002.mp3: your eyes are lined with black and a touch of red making them seem larger more dramatic but the final touch is the benny the crimson lipstick made from safflower petals a senior geisha applies it to your lower lip only a small perfect red bud this is a signal to everyone you are new you are an apprentice you are beautiful but you are not yet a woman you walk through the streets of the district visiting the teahouses and shops introducing yourself your every step is a performance your every glance is judged the pressure is immense one misstep one sign of fear and you bring shame to your okia your days now fall into a relentless rhythm of lessons you wake up before dawn after a simple breakfast of rice and miso soup you go to your classes you spend hours learning to play the shamisen a three-stringed instrument your fingertips crack and bleed but you don't stop you practice the slow gliding movements of the traditional dance the mai until your muscles scream you learn calligraphy the tea ceremony and the intricate rules of conversation you must be able to discuss politics with a government official poetry with a scholar and the price of rice with a merchant you are being sculpted into a living work of art and the process is grueling there is no room for failure everything you learn every kimono you wear every meal you eat is a debt a debt to the okia that you will spend years paying off
