[heard] nQoYJ_00003.mp3: as evening falls the transformation begins again the white mask is applied the heavy kimono is tied you and your sisters are called to an ozashki a banquet at a teahouse you enter the room a whirlwind of color and silk the air is thick with the smells of expensive food warm sake and men's cologne the men are powerful politicians businessmen famous artists you kneel on the tatami mat your back perfectly straight you are not here to eat the delicious food laid out before you you are here to serve you pour sake light cigarettes and laugh enchantingly your job is to make these men forget the outside world you play drinking games your movements quick and graceful you perform the dance you practiced all morning your fan fluttering like a butterfly you sing a song while your older sister plays the shamisen it's a delicate balance you must be charming but not familiar witty but not arrogant beautiful but not available you see the glances the men exchange you learn to read the room to understand who holds the power who is trying to impress whom you are a pawn in their games of status and also a coveted prize the more popular you are the more money you bring to your okia and the higher your own status rises but the tea house is also a battlefield the other maiko and geisha in the room are your sisters but they are also your rivals
