[heard] nQoYJ_00005.mp3: you remember the details of his business you ask about his interests you create an oasis of peace and beauty for him it can take months even years of carefully cultivated encounters at teahouses the okasan of your okia acts as a go-between negotiating the terms the decision is a massive gamble a kind and generous dana can give you a wonderful life a cruel or possessive one can make your existence a gilded cage there is a darker often misunderstood part of this journey for some maiko their coming of age is marked by a ceremony called mizuage it is in its starkest terms the practice of selling a maiko's virginity to the highest bidder this was not a universal practice and by the 1930s it was becoming less common but it was a harsh reality for many the money from the mizuage an enormous sum went directly to the okia it would instantly clear a huge portion of the young woman's debt catapulting her towards financial freedom for the girl it was a terrifying impersonal transaction that marked the final line between childhood and the harsh economic realities of her life it was a choice she did not make for herself after several years as a maiko usually around the age of 20 you undergo the ceremony of erikai the turning of the collar you trade your colorful long-sleeved kimono for a more subdued one your elaborate hairstyle is replaced with a simpler more elegant wig
